data.text:
Newcastle Upon Tyne, the UK

Latitude and longitude coordinates are: 54.966667, -1.600000.

Newcastle upon Tyne, usually known as just Newcastle, is a large city situated in North East England, the UK. It is a beautiful old settlement on the River Tyne, established in the early Middle Ages. It has always been a modern and progressive city, with plenty of educational establishments, research facilities and institutions, factories, business companies, etc. Newcastle is a part of a large urban area know as Tyneside, built in this part of the country, and it is a home to about 300,000 people, with the total number of residents of Tyneside close to 800,000 people. Education, retail trade, IT and other modern technology, business, and services contribute to the city's economy most. Newcastle is a popular tourist destination and is visited by hundred of thousands of people from around the world.
